:content
<br>
Tooltip on words&#58; 3 arguments. <ul>
 <li>Argument 1&#58; the prompt
 </li>
 <li>Argument 2 (facultatif)&#58; the options of the tooltip between <tt>[ ]</tt>. 
 If the word <tt>nojs</tt> is added (outside the brackets), the used javascript
is not reload (it is sufficient to load it onec at the begining of
the html page). 
The available options are at the adress 
<a href=http&#58;//www.walterzorn.com target=wims_external>www.walterzorn.com</a>,
 see also the help of Createxo.
 </li>
 <li>Argument 3 &#58; the text inside the tooltip.
</li>
</ul>
If all arguments are empty, only the javascript is loaded.
You may change the style of the prompt by using 
html balises or by defining the css style class <tt>span.tooltip</tt>.
<p>
For example&#58;
<pre>
\tooltip{ }
\tooltip{word1}{nojs}{help1}
\tooltip{&lt;font color="brown">word2&lt;/font>}{nojs [FONTSIZE, '20pt', ABOVE, 'true']}{help2}
\tooltip{word3}{[FONTSIZE, '40pt', ABOVE, 'false']}{help3}
\tooltip{word4}{ }{help4}
</pre>
<p>

!read primitives.phtml 1, tooltip,  


!read primitives.phtml 2, tooltip, word1, nojs, help1 


!read primitives.phtml 3, tooltip, <font color="brown">word2</font>, nojs [FONTSIZE, '20pt', ABOVE, 'true'], help2 


!read primitives.phtml 4, tooltip, word3, [FONTSIZE, '40pt', ABOVE, 'false'], help3 


!read primitives.phtml 5, tooltip, word4, , help4 

